cyan【🩵】resident weeb・rap nerd
isn't account theft also a problem with discriminators, they could have the same username but different number and some people might not be aware (but i guess that's their problem)
OOPS! Studio! 2023-05-04 3:55 AM
No, that's definitely not a problem for account theft. If someone wants to steal your account they know your username either way. Two people sharing a username doesn't increase the ease of account theft. It increases the chance that someone will accidentally sign into someone else's account, but that's really not an issue. Plus Discord doesn't use usernames for login anyway - they use emails. And emails need to be unique. So either way, there's no way that could be a problem, neither maliciously nor accidentally (edited)
